# IndexedDB Rules

## Library
Always use the `idb` npm package — never use raw `indexedDB` global directly.

```typescript
import { openDB, DBSchema, IDBPDatabase } from 'idb';
```

## Schema Definition
Define a typed schema interface extending `DBSchema`:

```typescript
interface EmailEditorDB extends DBSchema {
  templates: {
    key: string; // id (uuid)
    value: Template;
    indexes: {
      'by-alias': string;
      'by-updatedAt': number;
    };
  };
}
```

## DB Initialization
- Export a single `getDB()` function that lazily opens the DB
- Always specify the DB version — increment when schema changes
- Handle `upgrade` callback for creating/migrating object stores

```typescript
const DB_NAME = 'email-editor-db';
const DB_VERSION = 1;

let dbPromise: Promise<IDBPDatabase<EmailEditorDB>> | null = null;

export function getDB() {
  if (!dbPromise) {
    dbPromise = openDB<EmailEditorDB>(DB_NAME, DB_VERSION, {
      upgrade(db) {
        const store = db.createObjectStore('templates', { keyPath: 'id' });
        store.createIndex('by-alias', 'alias', { unique: true });
        store.createIndex('by-updatedAt', 'updatedAt');
      },
    });
  }
  return dbPromise;
}
```

## CRUD Patterns
Always wrap DB operations in try/catch. Return typed results.

```typescript
// GET ALL
export async function getAllTemplates(): Promise<Template[]> {
  try {
    const db = await getDB();
    return db.getAllFromIndex('templates', 'by-updatedAt');
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Failed to get templates:', err);
    return [];
  }
}

// UPSERT
export async function saveTemplate(template: Template): Promise<void> {
  const db = await getDB();
  await db.put('templates', { ...template, updatedAt: Date.now() });
}

// DELETE
export async function deleteTemplate(id: string): Promise<void> {
  const db = await getDB();
  await db.delete('templates', id);
}
```

## Rules
- Never mutate objects retrieved from IndexedDB — clone before editing
- Always update `updatedAt` on save
- Generate `id` using `crypto.randomUUID()` for new records
- Do NOT use localStorage or sessionStorage — IndexedDB only
